<html><head></head><body><b>Henri Becquerel (1852–1908)</b><br/>
French physicist. <br/>In 1872 commenced his studies, which he completed in 1888 obtaining a doctoral degree. In his early works he dealt with properties of light <br/>such as polarisation, phosphorescence <br/>and absorption in crystals. Later, he focused on natural radioactivity. He published his works in numerous scientific journals. In 1878 his son was born – he also became a physicist, thus initiating <br/>the fourth generation <br/>of physicists in the family.</body></html>